hwBFDMIB.name: hwBFDMIB

revisions.description: V1.47, modified the revision history.
V1.46, modified the date of copyright.

V1.45, add hwBfdDynamicSessionTos for dynamic session tos in hwBfdScalarsObjects, add hwBfdv6MultiHopSessUpTrap,hwBfdv6MultiHopSessDownTrap for IPv6 MultiHop. Add hwBfdSessPeerAddr,hwBfdSessBindType,hwBfdSessVrfIndex for hwBfdSessUpTrap and hwBfdSessDownTrap, add hwBfdv6SingleHopSessUpTrap,hwBfdv6SingleHopSessDownTrap for IPv6 SingleHop. Add hwBfdDynamicSessionTos for dynamic session tos.
V1.44, modified the scope of hwBfdIfConfName .
V1.43, modified the description of hwBfdSessBindAppTypeMask for VTE/VPW/FRP/BGPLSP.
V1.42, modified the value and the description of hwBfdSessConfBindType for new bfd type bgpTunnel, modified the value and the description of hwBfdSessBindType for new bfd type bgpTunnel.
V1.41, modified the value and the description of hwBfdSessConfBindType for new bfd type ldpTunnel, modified the value and the description of hwBfdSessBindType for new bfd type ldpTunnel.

V1.40, add hwBfdStaticSessionTos for static session tos. Add hwBfdDynamicSessionTosEx for extend hwBfdDynamicSessionTos. Add hwBfdSessConfTOSEx for extend hwBfdSessConfTOS. Add hwBfdSessDscp to display dscp value when it is enable in a bfd session.
V1.25, add hwBfdSessBindAppTypeMask.
V1.24, add hwBfdDynamicSessionTos for dynamic session tos.
V1.23, modified BfdInterval to Integer32.

V1.22, removed the range of hwBfdSessActualRxInterval, hwBfdSessActualTxInterval, added the default value of hwBfdAdminStatus, hwBfdSessConfWTRInterval, hwBfdSessDetectMult, hwBfdSessDiscrAuto, hwBfdSessDynamicNumber, hwBfdSessInterfaceLimitNumber, hwBfdSessLimitNumber, hwBfdSessStaticNumber, hwBfdVersionNumber.
V1.21, modified the description of hwBfdIfConfEnable, hwBfdSessConfWTRInterval, hwBfdSessConfPSTFlag.
V1.20, modified for bfd mib standardization.
V1.19, updated the description and format.
V1.18, modified the trap nodes of hwBfdSessGroupUpTrap and hwBfdSessGroupDownTrap. Updated the description and format.
V1.17, modified BfdInterval to Unsigned32.
V1.16, modified hwBfdSessConfRemoteDiscr and hwBfdSessRemoteDiscr's range from 1...16384 to 0...4294967295.
V1.15, modified the description and format.
V1.14, modified syntax of hwBfdSessPerfLastSessDownTime and hwBfdSessionPerStartTime.
V1.13, modified description of all leaves.
V1.12, updated the description and format.
V1.11, modified syntax of hwBfdSessPerfLastSessDownTime and hwBfdSessionPerStartTime.
V1.10, added four trap nodes of hwBfdSessUpTrap, hwBfdSessDownTrap, hwBfdSessGroupUpTrap and hwBfdSessGroupDownTrap.
V1.09, changed the range of leaves hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinRxInterval and hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinRxInterval.
V1.08, changed the range of leaf hwBfdSessRemoteDiscr as 0-4294967295.
V1.07, added flagNoPW, entireDynamic, staticAuto enum.
V1.06, added leaf hwBfdSessConfVlanID in table hwBfdSessionTable and changed the attribute of leaf hwBfdSessConfBindIfIndex as read-create.
V1.00, initial version.

hwBFDMIB.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwBFDMIB.description: MIB interface of BFD protocol configuration. The Bidirectional Forwarding Detection (BFD) protocol is standardized by the IETF. BFD detects the traffic forwarding capability of the link or system by quickly sending BFD control packets (the UDP packets in a specified format) at intervals between two nodes.

BfdDiag.name: BfdDiag
BfdDiag.description: Diagnostic code specifying the local system's reason for the last session state changed.

hwBfdVersionNumber.name: hwBfdVersionNumber
hwBfdVersionNumber.description: The current version number of the BFD protocol is 1. Default: 1

hwBfdAdminStatus.name: hwBfdAdminStatus
hwBfdAdminStatus.description: Describe the administrative status of a BFD protocol. Options: 1. enabled(1) -denotes that the BFD Process is active on all interface 2. disabled(2) -denotes that the BFD process is disabled on all interfaces Default: 2

hwBfdSessLimitNumber.name: hwBfdSessLimitNumber
hwBfdSessLimitNumber.description: Define the maximum number of BFD sessions allowed in the logic router. Default: 0

hwBfdSessInterfaceLimitNumber.name: hwBfdSessInterfaceLimitNumber
hwBfdSessInterfaceLimitNumber.description: Define the maximum number of BFD sessions allowed per board. Default: 0

hwBfdSessStaticNumber.name: hwBfdSessStaticNumber
hwBfdSessStaticNumber.description: The total number of BFD static sessions. Default: 0

hwBfdSessDynamicNumber.name: hwBfdSessDynamicNumber
hwBfdSessDynamicNumber.description: The total number of BFD dynamic sessions. Default: 0

hwBfdSessGlobalDefaultIpAddr.name: hwBfdSessGlobalDefaultIpAddr
hwBfdSessGlobalDefaultIpAddr.description: Define the default multicast IP address used in BFD multicast detection. Default: 0

hwBfdEchoPassiveStatus.name: hwBfdEchoPassiveStatus
hwBfdEchoPassiveStatus.description: The passive Echo function of BFD. Options: 1. enabled(1) -denotes that the BFD EchoPassive capability is enabled 2. disabled(2) -denotes that the BFD EchoPassive capability is disabled Default: 2

hwBfdEchoAclNum.name: hwBfdEchoAclNum
hwBfdEchoAclNum.description: The Acl Number for passive Echo function of BFD. Default: 0

hwBfdSessDynamicPingInterval.name: hwBfdSessDynamicPingInterval
hwBfdSessDynamicPingInterval.description: Define the sending interval of the MPLS echo packet. Default: 60 Unit: second

hwBfdSessDynamicSupportPassive.name: hwBfdSessDynamicSupportPassive
hwBfdSessDynamicSupportPassive.description: The capability of automatically creating BFD sessions on the LSP egress. Options: 1. enabled(1) -denotes that the egress can create BFD sessions 2. disabled(2) -denotes that the egress can not create BFD sessions Default: 2

hwBfdSessDelayUpTime.name: hwBfdSessDelayUpTime
hwBfdSessDelayUpTime.description: Define delay interval before the session turns to up. Unit: second Default: 0

hwBfdSessMultiDstPort.name: hwBfdSessMultiDstPort
hwBfdSessMultiDstPort.description: The destination UDP port of multi-hop BFD session. When the administrative status of BFD protocol is disabled, this value will be 0. Default: 3784

hwBfdTrapSendInterval.name: hwBfdTrapSendInterval
hwBfdTrapSendInterval.description: Define the sending interval of TRAP message. Unit: second Default: 120

hwBfdLimitDeviceName.name: hwBfdLimitDeviceName
hwBfdLimitDeviceName.description: The device name which session number reached up limit.

hwBfdDynamicSessionTos.name: hwBfdDynamicSessionTos
hwBfdDynamicSessionTos.description: The Tos-Exp of dynamic session. Default: 7

hwBfdStaticSessionTos.name: hwBfdStaticSessionTos
hwBfdStaticSessionTos.description: The Tos-Exp of static session. Default: 7

hwBfdDynamicSessionTosEx.name: hwBfdDynamicSessionTosEx
hwBfdDynamicSessionTosEx.description: The extended Tos-Exp of dynamic session. Default: 7

hwBfdIfConfTable.name: hwBfdIfConfTable
hwBfdIfConfTable.description: The interface configuration table of BFD. The index of this table is hwBfdIfConfIndex.

hwBfdIfConfEntry.name: hwBfdIfConfEntry
hwBfdIfConfEntry.description: The interface configuration table of BFD. The index of this entry is hwBfdIfConfIndex.

hwBfdIfConfIndex.name: hwBfdIfConfIndex
hwBfdIfConfIndex.description: It is the configuration index of this interface. This index is automatically allocated inside the system and is not user-configurable.

hwBfdIfConfName.name: hwBfdIfConfName
hwBfdIfConfName.description: It is the name of this Interface.

hwBfdIfConfEnable.name: hwBfdIfConfEnable
hwBfdIfConfEnable.description: The flag whether the interface has enabled BFD. Options: 1. disable(0) -Indicates that the interface has disabled BFD 2. enable(1) -Indicates that the interface has enabled BFD

hwBfdIfConfDeleting.name: hwBfdIfConfDeleting
hwBfdIfConfDeleting.description: The flag that whether the interface is in deleting. Options: 1. notDeleted(0) -the interface is not deleted 2. deleted(1) -the interface is deleted

hwBfdIfConfAvailable.name: hwBfdIfConfAvailable
hwBfdIfConfAvailable.description: The flag that whether the interface is available. Options: 1. notAvailable(0) -the interface is not available 2. available(1) -the interface is available

hwBfdIfConfSessCnt.name: hwBfdIfConfSessCnt
hwBfdIfConfSessCnt.description: The number of sessions that has been bound to this interface.

hwBfdIfConfRowStatus.name: hwBfdIfConfRowStatus
hwBfdIfConfRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows.

hwBfdSessionConfTable.name: hwBfdSessionConfTable
hwBfdSessionConfTable.description: BFD Session Configuration Table. Use this table to get/configure BFD sessions. The index of this table is hwBfdSessConfName.

hwBfdSessionConfEntry.name: hwBfdSessionConfEntry
hwBfdSessionConfEntry.description: BFD Session Configuration Table. Use this table to get/configure BFD sessions. The index of this entry is hwBfdSessConfName.

hwBfdSessConfName.name: hwBfdSessConfName
hwBfdSessConfName.description: It is the name of this configuration model.

hwBfdSessConfMIndex.name: hwBfdSessConfMIndex
hwBfdSessConfMIndex.description: It is the configuration index of this session.

hwBfdSessConfLocalDiscr.name: hwBfdSessConfLocalDiscr
hwBfdSessConfLocalDiscr.description: Define the local discriminator of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfRemoteDiscr.name: hwBfdSessConfRemoteDiscr
hwBfdSessConfRemoteDiscr.description: Define the remote discriminator of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfPeerAddr.name: hwBfdSessConfPeerAddr
hwBfdSessConfPeerAddr.description: Define the IP address of the peer in the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfBindIfIndex.name: hwBfdSessConfBindIfIndex
hwBfdSessConfBindIfIndex.description: It is the index of the binding interface in the BFD configuration.

hwBfdSessConfBindIfName.name: hwBfdSessConfBindIfName
hwBfdSessConfBindIfName.description: It is the name of the binding interface in the BFD configuration.

hwBfdSessConfDemandEnable.name: hwBfdSessConfDemandEnable
hwBfdSessConfDemandEnable.description: It is the flag of the BFD demand mode. Options: 1. disabled(0) -disable the BFD demand mode 2. enabled(1) -enable the BFD demand mode

hwBfdSessConfDemandTimerInterval.name: hwBfdSessConfDemandTimerInterval
hwBfdSessConfDemandTimerInterval.description: Define the detecting interval in the BFD session with the demand mode. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessConfDetectMult.name: hwBfdSessConfDetectMult
hwBfdSessConfDetectMult.description: It is Detect time multiplier of the configuration. The negotiated transmit interval, multiplied by this value, provides the detection time for the transmitting system in Asynchronous mode.

hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinRxInterval.name: hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinRxInterval
hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinRxInterval.description: This is the minimum interval of the configuration,in milliseconds, between received BFD Control packets that this system is capable of supporting. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinTxInterval.name: hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinTxInterval
hwBfdSessConfDesiredMinTxInterval.description: This is the minimum interval of the configuration, in milliseconds, that the local system would like to use when transmitting BFD Control packets. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessConfWTRInterval.name: hwBfdSessConfWTRInterval
hwBfdSessConfWTRInterval.description: The wait-to-restore (WTR) time of the BFD session. The event that indicates the session changing into the Up state is reported to the application program only after the WTR times out. Unit: minute

hwBfdSessConfTOS.name: hwBfdSessConfTOS
hwBfdSessConfTOS.description: This is the TOS value of bfd packet.

hwBfdSessConfPSTFlag.name: hwBfdSessConfPSTFlag
hwBfdSessConfPSTFlag.description: The PST flag of the BFD session configuration. It indicates the status association between the current BFD session and the interface bound to the session. Options: 1. disabled(0) -indicates that the PST capability of the BFD session is disabled 2. enabled(1) -indicates that the PST capability of the BFD session is enabled

hwBfdSessConfCommitFlag.name: hwBfdSessConfCommitFlag
hwBfdSessConfCommitFlag.description: It is the commit flag of the configuration entry. Options: 1. notCommit(0) -not commit 2. commit(1) -commit

hwBfdSessConfAdminStatus.name: hwBfdSessConfAdminStatus
hwBfdSessConfAdminStatus.description: A BFD session can be administratively enabled or disabled. The AdminStatus field indicates the BFD session status. Options: 1. 0 -disable 2. 1 -enable

hwBfdSessConfRowStatus.name: hwBfdSessConfRowStatus
hwBfdSessConfRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows.

hwBfdSessConfSourceAddr.name: hwBfdSessConfSourceAddr
hwBfdSessConfSourceAddr.description: Define the source IP address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfVrfIndex.name: hwBfdSessConfVrfIndex
hwBfdSessConfVrfIndex.description: The index of the VPN interface.

hwBfdSessConfDefaultIp.name: hwBfdSessConfDefaultIp
hwBfdSessConfDefaultIp.description: BFD session use default multicast IP as the detect peer-ip Options: 1. no(1) -do not use the default multicast IP 2. yes(2) -use the default multicast IP

hwBfdSessConfPISFlag.name: hwBfdSessConfPISFlag
hwBfdSessConfPISFlag.description: The state of BFD session is associated with the state of the binding interface Options: 1. false(1) -do not associate with interface state 2. true(2) -associate with interface state 3. subif(3) -associate with interface and correlative sub interface

hwBfdSessConfBindType.name: hwBfdSessConfBindType
hwBfdSessConfBindType.description: The binding type of the BFD session. Options: 1. interfaceIp(1) -BFD for IP with peer-ip and interface 2. peerIp(2) -BFD for IP only with peer-ip 3. sourceIp(3) -BFD for IP with peer-ip and source-ip 4. ifAndSourceIp(4) -BFD for IP with peer-ip, interface and source-ip 5. fec(5) -BFD for FEC(NOT support now) 6. tunnelIf(6) -BFD for Tunnel interface(NOT support now) 7. ospf(7) -BFD for OSPF 8. isis(8) -BFD for ISIS 9. ldpLsp(9) -BFD for LDP-LSP 10. staticLsp(10) -BFD for static LSP 11. teLsp(11) -BFD for TE-LSP 12. teTunnel(12) -BFD for TE-Tunnel 13. pw(13) -BFD for PW 14. vsiPw(15) -BFD for VSI PW 15. ldpTunnel(21) -BFD for LDP-Tunnel 16. bgpTunnel(22) -BFD for BGP-Tunnel

hwBfdSessConfNextHop.name: hwBfdSessConfNextHop
hwBfdSessConfNextHop.description: It is the next hop of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfStaticLspName.name: hwBfdSessConfStaticLspName
hwBfdSessConfStaticLspName.description: It is the static LSP name of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfPWSecondaryFlag.name: hwBfdSessConfPWSecondaryFlag
hwBfdSessConfPWSecondaryFlag.description: The role of the PW bound with BFD session. Options: 1. flagMasterPW(1) -master PW 2. flagSecondaryPW(2)-secondary PW 3. flagNoPW(3) -no PW

hwBfdSessConfTunnelDetectType.name: hwBfdSessConfTunnelDetectType
hwBfdSessConfTunnelDetectType.description: Set the failure notifies policy type. Options: 1. flagBothDown(1) -notify applications when detecting both Detect-Down and Neighbor-Down 2. flagNeighborDown(2) -notify applications only when detecting Neighbor-Down

hwBfdSessConfVcId.name: hwBfdSessConfVcId
hwBfdSessConfVcId.description: It is the ID of VC.

hwBfdSessConfVsiName.name: hwBfdSessConfVsiName
hwBfdSessConfVsiName.description: It is the name of VSI.

hwBfdSessConfVsiPeerAddr.name: hwBfdSessConfVsiPeerAddr
hwBfdSessConfVsiPeerAddr.description: It is the peer-ip of VSI.

hwBfdSessConfDiscrAuto.name: hwBfdSessConfDiscrAuto
hwBfdSessConfDiscrAuto.description: Describe whether the discriminator can be auto allocated. Options: 1.enabled(1) -the discriminator can be allocated automatically 2.disabled(2) -the discriminator can not be allocated automatically

hwBfdSessConfPeerIpv6Addr.name: hwBfdSessConfPeerIpv6Addr
hwBfdSessConfPeerIpv6Addr.description: Define the peer IPv6 address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfSourceIpv6Addr.name: hwBfdSessConfSourceIpv6Addr
hwBfdSessConfSourceIpv6Addr.description: Define the source IPv6 address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfIpv6NextHop.name: hwBfdSessConfIpv6NextHop
hwBfdSessConfIpv6NextHop.description: It is the next hop of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfIsIpv6Addr.name: hwBfdSessConfIsIpv6Addr
hwBfdSessConfIsIpv6Addr.description: Whether the peer address of the BFD session is IPv6 address.

hwBfdSessConfKeychainName.name: hwBfdSessConfKeychainName
hwBfdSessConfKeychainName.description: Specify the name of the keychain for authentication.

hwBfdSessConfMeticulous.name: hwBfdSessConfMeticulous
hwBfdSessConfMeticulous.description: Whether enable meticulous authentication for MD5 or SHA-1 type. Options: 1. enabled(1) -enable meticulous authentication for MD5 or SHA-1 type 2. disabled(2) -disabled meticulous authentication for MD5 or SHA-1 type

hwBfdSessConfLooseAuthentication.name: hwBfdSessConfLooseAuthentication
hwBfdSessConfLooseAuthentication.description: Whether loose authentication check. Options: 1.True(1) -loose-check 2.False(2) -do not loose-check

hwBfdSessConfOneArmEcho.name: hwBfdSessConfOneArmEcho
hwBfdSessConfOneArmEcho.description: The value of this object identifies whether a session works in one-arm-echo mode. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates that the session works in one-arm-echo mode 2. disabled(2) -indicates that the session does not work in one-arm-echo mode

hwBfdSessConfMinEchoRxInterval.name: hwBfdSessConfMinEchoRxInterval
hwBfdSessConfMinEchoRxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the minimum interval between received BFD Control packets, in milliseconds.This value reflects the capability of receiving BFD Control packets. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessConfPWTtlMode.name: hwBfdSessConfPWTtlMode
hwBfdSessConfPWTtlMode.description: The value of this object identifies the configuration mode of a TTL used by the BFD session for PW. Options: 1. config(1) -indicates that the TTL is manually set 2. auto(2) -indicates that the TTL is automatically calculated based on an IP address 3. default(3)-indicates that the TTL is 255 by default 4. none(4) -indicates that the TTL is not in PW mode

hwBfdSessConfPWTtl.name: hwBfdSessConfPWTtl
hwBfdSessConfPWTtl.description: The value of this object identifies the TTL used by the BFD session for PW. The vlaue is configurable only when the configuration mode of a TTL is config.

hwBfdSessConfRemotePeerIpType.name: hwBfdSessConfRemotePeerIpType
hwBfdSessConfRemotePeerIpType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of the destination address of the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessConfRemotePeerIp.name: hwBfdSessConfRemotePeerIp
hwBfdSessConfRemotePeerIp.description: The value of this object identifies the destination IP address of the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessConfSelectBoard.name: hwBfdSessConfSelectBoard
hwBfdSessConfSelectBoard.description: This object indicates the main processing board of a BFD session.

hwBfdSessConfPWSPE.name: hwBfdSessConfPWSPE
hwBfdSessConfPWSPE.description: The value of this object identifies the node on which a BFD session is set up. The values are as follows. Options: 1. upe(1) -indicates that a BFD session is set up on a UPE to detect a PW 2. spe(2) -indicates that a BFD session is set up on an SPE to detect a PW 3. none(3) -indicates that a BFD session does not detect a PW Default: none

hwBfdSessConfPWTrackIfName.name: hwBfdSessConfPWTrackIfName
hwBfdSessConfPWTrackIfName.description: This object indicates the interface monitored by the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessConfIsPWTrackIf.name: hwBfdSessConfIsPWTrackIf
hwBfdSessConfIsPWTrackIf.description: The value of this object identifies whether the BFD session for PW monitors an interface. The values are as follows. Options: 1. enabled(1) -enables the BFD session for PW to monitor the interface 2. disabled(2)-disables the BFD session for PW from monitoring the interface

hwBfdSessConfEncapsulationType.name: hwBfdSessConfEncapsulationType
hwBfdSessConfEncapsulationType.description: The value of this object identifies the VC encapsulation type on an SPE. The values are as follows: fr atm-aal5-sdu atm-trans-cell vlan ethernet hdlc ppp atm-nto1-vcc atm-nto1-vpc ip-layer2 atm-1to1-vcc atm-1to1-vpc atm-aal5-pdu satop-e1 satop-t1 esopsn-basic ip-interworking

hwBfdSessConfPEVid.name: hwBfdSessConfPEVid
hwBfdSessConfPEVid.description: The value of this object identifies the outer tag of a sub-interface for QinQ VLAN tag termination or the VLAN ID of a sub-interface for dot1q VLAN tag termination.

hwBfdSessConfCEVid.name: hwBfdSessConfCEVid
hwBfdSessConfCEVid.description: The value of this object identifies the inner tag in QinQ packets.

hwBfdSessConfTOSEx.name: hwBfdSessConfTOSEx
hwBfdSessConfTOSEx.description: This is the extended TOS value of bfd packet.

hwBfdSessionTable.name: hwBfdSessionTable
hwBfdSessionTable.description: The BFD Session Table describes the BFD sessions. The index of this table is hwBfdSessIndex.

hwBfdSessionEntry.name: hwBfdSessionEntry
hwBfdSessionEntry.description: The BFD Session Table describes the BFD sessions. The index of this entry is hwBfdSessIndex.

hwBfdSessIndex.name: hwBfdSessIndex
hwBfdSessIndex.description: It is unique and the Index of this session. This index is automatically allocated inside the system and is not user-configurable.

hwBfdSessMIndex.name: hwBfdSessMIndex
hwBfdSessMIndex.description: This value indicate the configuration has Main Index.

hwBfdSessBindVRRP.name: hwBfdSessBindVRRP
hwBfdSessBindVRRP.description: Describe the capability of bound with VRRP for the BFD session. Options: 1. notBind(0) -not bind 2. bind(1) -bind

hwBfdSessCfgName.name: hwBfdSessCfgName
hwBfdSessCfgName.description: This indicate the name of the session which will be display course information or statistic information of the session.

hwBfdSessPeerAddr.name: hwBfdSessPeerAddr
hwBfdSessPeerAddr.description: Define the peer IP address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessBindIfIndex.name: hwBfdSessBindIfIndex
hwBfdSessBindIfIndex.description: It is the index of the binding interface in the BFD session

hwBfdSessBindIfName.name: hwBfdSessBindIfName
hwBfdSessBindIfName.description: It is the name of the binding interface in the BFD session.

hwBfdSessLocalDiscr.name: hwBfdSessLocalDiscr
hwBfdSessLocalDiscr.description: A unique, nonzero discriminator value generated by the transmitting system, used to demultiplex multiple BFD sessions between the same pair of system.

hwBfdSessRemoteDiscr.name: hwBfdSessRemoteDiscr
hwBfdSessRemoteDiscr.description: The discriminator received from the corresponding remote system. This field reflects back the received value of My Discriminator, or is zero if that value is unknown.

hwBfdSessOperMode.name: hwBfdSessOperMode
hwBfdSessOperMode.description: Describe the current operating mode configured with the BFD session. Options: 1. 0 -asynchronous mode with echo function 2. 1 -asynchronous mode without echo function 3. 2 -demand mode with echo function 4. 3 -demand mode without echo function 5. 4 -asynchronous One-arm-echo mode

hwBfdSessDetectMult.name: hwBfdSessDetectMult
hwBfdSessDetectMult.description: Detect time multiplier. The negotiated transmit interval, multiplied by this value, provides the detection time for the transmitting system in Asynchronous mode. Default: 3

hwBfdSessDemandTimerInterval.name: hwBfdSessDemandTimerInterval
hwBfdSessDemandTimerInterval.description: It is the detecting interval in the BFD session with the demand mode. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessActualRxInterval.name: hwBfdSessActualRxInterval
hwBfdSessActualRxInterval.description: This is the minimum interval, in milliseconds, between received BFD Control packets that this system is capable of supporting. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessActualTxInterval.name: hwBfdSessActualTxInterval
hwBfdSessActualTxInterval.description: This is the minimum interval, in milliseconds, that the local system would like to use when transmitting BFD Control packets. Unit: millisecond

hwBfdSessWTRInterval.name: hwBfdSessWTRInterval
hwBfdSessWTRInterval.description: The WTR interval of the BFD session. Unit: minute

hwBfdSessTOS.name: hwBfdSessTOS
hwBfdSessTOS.description: This is the TOS value of bfd packet.

hwBfdSessState.name: hwBfdSessState
hwBfdSessState.description: Describe the current state of the BFD session. Options: 1. 0 -admin down 2. 1 -down 3. 2 -init 4. 3 -up

hwBfdSessDiag.name: hwBfdSessDiag
hwBfdSessDiag.description: A diagnostic code specifying the local system's reason for the last session state change. Options: 1. 0 -no diagnostic 2. 1 -control detection time expired 3. 2 -echo function failed 4. 3 -neighbor signaled session down 5. 4 -forwarding plane reset 6. 5 -path down 7. 6 -concatenated path down 8. 7 -administratively down 9. 8 -reverse concatenated path down 10. 9 -neighbor signaled session down (receive admindown) 11. 10-31 -reserved for future use

hwBfdSessSourceAddr.name: hwBfdSessSourceAddr
hwBfdSessSourceAddr.description: The source address of the session.

hwBfdSessVrfIndex.name: hwBfdSessVrfIndex
hwBfdSessVrfIndex.description: The index of the VPN interface.

hwBfdSessType.name: hwBfdSessType
hwBfdSessType.description: The type of the BFD session. Options: 1. static(1) -static 2. dynamic(2) -dynamic 3. entireDynamic(3) -entire dynamic 4. auto(4) -auto

hwBfdSessBindAppType.name: hwBfdSessBindAppType

hwBfdSessDefaultIp.name: hwBfdSessDefaultIp
hwBfdSessDefaultIp.description: BFD session use default multicast IP as the detect peer-ip Options: 1. no(1) -do not use the default multicast IP 2. yes(2) -use the default multicast IP

hwBfdSessPISFlag.name: hwBfdSessPISFlag
hwBfdSessPISFlag.description: The state of BFD session is associated with the state of the binding interface Options: 1. false(1) -do not associate with interface state 2. true(2) -ssociate with interface state 3. subif(3) -associate with interface and correlative sub interface

hwBfdSessBindType.name: hwBfdSessBindType
hwBfdSessBindType.description: The binding type of the BFD session. Options: 1. interfaceIp(1) -BFD for IP with peer-ip and interface 2. peerIp(2) -BFD for IP only with peer-ip 3. sourceIp(3) -BFD for IP with peer-ip and source-ip 4. ifAndSourceIp(4) -BFD for IP with peer-ip, interface and source-ip 5. fec(5) -BFD for FEC(NOT support now) 6. tunnelIf(6) -BFD for Tunnel interface(NOT support now) 7. ospf(7) -BFD for OSPF 8. isis(8) -BFD for ISIS 9. ldpLsp(9) -BFD for LDP-LSP 10. staticLsp(10) -BFD for static LSP 11. teLsp(11) -BFD for TE-LSP 12. teTunnel(12) -BFD for TE-Tunnel 13. pw(13) -BFD for PW; 14. vsiPw(15) -BFD for VSI PW 15. ldpTunnel(21) -BFD for LDP-Tunnel 16. bgpTunnel(22) -BFD for BGP-Tunnel

hwBfdSessNextHop.name: hwBfdSessNextHop
hwBfdSessNextHop.description: It is the next hop of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessStaticLspName.name: hwBfdSessStaticLspName
hwBfdSessStaticLspName.description: It is the static LSP name of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessLspIndex.name: hwBfdSessLspIndex
hwBfdSessLspIndex.description: It is the index of the static LSP or LDP LSP in BFD session, mapping the channel index in MPLS network.

hwBfdSessPWSecondaryFlag.name: hwBfdSessPWSecondaryFlag
hwBfdSessPWSecondaryFlag.description: The role of the PW bound with BFD session. Options: 1. flagMasterPW(1) -master PW 2. flagSecondaryPW(2) -secondary PW 3. flagNoPW(3) -no PW Default: 1

hwBfdSessTunnelDetectType.name: hwBfdSessTunnelDetectType
hwBfdSessTunnelDetectType.description: Set the failure notifies policy type. Options: 1. flagBothDown(1) -notify applications when detecting both Detect-Down and Neighbor-Down 2. flagNeighborDown(2) -notify applications only when detecting Neighbor-Down Default: 1

hwBfdSessVcId.name: hwBfdSessVcId
hwBfdSessVcId.description: It is the ID of VC.

hwBfdSessVsiName.name: hwBfdSessVsiName
hwBfdSessVsiName.description: It is the name of VSI.

hwBfdSessVsiPeerAddr.name: hwBfdSessVsiPeerAddr
hwBfdSessVsiPeerAddr.description: It is the peer-ip of VSI.

hwBfdSessDiscrAuto.name: hwBfdSessDiscrAuto
hwBfdSessDiscrAuto.description: Describe whether the discriminator can be auto allocated. Options: 1. enabled(1) -the discriminator can be allocated automatically 2. disabled(2) -the discriminator can not be allocated automatically Default: disabled

hwBfdSessPeerIpv6Addr.name: hwBfdSessPeerIpv6Addr
hwBfdSessPeerIpv6Addr.description: Define the peer IPv6 address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessSourceIpv6Addr.name: hwBfdSessSourceIpv6Addr
hwBfdSessSourceIpv6Addr.description: Define the source IPv6 address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessIpv6NextHop.name: hwBfdSessIpv6NextHop
hwBfdSessIpv6NextHop.description: It is the next hop of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessIsIPv6Addr.name: hwBfdSessIsIPv6Addr
hwBfdSessIsIPv6Addr.description: Whether the peer address of the BFD session is IPv6 address. Default: false

hwBfdSessMeticulous.name: hwBfdSessMeticulous
hwBfdSessMeticulous.description: Whether enable meticulous authentication for MD5 or SHA-1 type. Options: 1. enabled(1) -enable meticulous authentication for MD5 or SHA-1 type 2. disabled(2) -disabled meticulous authentication for MD5 or SHA-1 type Default: 2

hwBfdSessLooseAuthentication.name: hwBfdSessLooseAuthentication
hwBfdSessLooseAuthentication.description: Whether loose authentication check. Options: 1. True(1) -loose-check 2. False(2) -do not loose-check Default: false

hwBfdSessAuthenticationStatus.name: hwBfdSessAuthenticationStatus
hwBfdSessAuthenticationStatus.description: Authentication status of the bfd session Options: 1. 0 -authentication disable 2. 1 -interface board do not support bfd authentication 3. 2 -keychain does not exist 4. 3 -auth BFD session number exceed 5. 4 -authentication in operation normally 100. 100 -exception Default: 0

hwBfdSessOneArmEcho.name: hwBfdSessOneArmEcho
hwBfdSessOneArmEcho.description: The value of this object identifies whether a session works in one-arm-echo mode. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates that the session works in one-arm-echo mode 2. disabled(2) -indicates that the session does not work in one-arm-echo mode Default: disabled

hwBfdSessPWTtlMode.name: hwBfdSessPWTtlMode
hwBfdSessPWTtlMode.description: The value of this object identifies the configuration mode of a TTL used by the BFD session for PW. Options: 1. config(1) -indicates that the TTL is manually set 2. auto(2) -indicates that the TTL is automatically calculated based on an IP address 3. default(3) -indicates that the TTL is 255 by default 4. nottl(4) -indicates that the TTL is not in PW mode

hwBfdSessPWTtl.name: hwBfdSessPWTtl
hwBfdSessPWTtl.description: The value of this object identifies the TTL used by the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessRemotePeerIpType.name: hwBfdSessRemotePeerIpType
hwBfdSessRemotePeerIpType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of the destination address of the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessRemotePeerIp.name: hwBfdSessRemotePeerIp
hwBfdSessRemotePeerIp.description: The value of this object identifies the destination IP address of the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessSelectBoard.name: hwBfdSessSelectBoard
hwBfdSessSelectBoard.description: This object indicates the main processing board of a BFD session.

hwBfdSessPWSPE.name: hwBfdSessPWSPE
hwBfdSessPWSPE.description: The value of this object identifies the node on which a BFD session is set up. The values are as follows. Options: 1. upe(1) -indicates that a BFD session is set up on a UPE to detect a PW 2. spe(2) -indicates that a BFD session is set up on an SPE to detect a PW 3. none(3) -indicates that a BFD session does not detect a PW Default: none

hwBfdSessPWTrackIfName.name: hwBfdSessPWTrackIfName
hwBfdSessPWTrackIfName.description: This object indicates the interface monitored by the BFD session for PW.

hwBfdSessIsPWTrackIf.name: hwBfdSessIsPWTrackIf
hwBfdSessIsPWTrackIf.description: The value of this object identifies whether the BFD session for PW monitors an interface. The values are as follows. Options: 1. enabled(1) -enables the BFD session for PW to monitor the interface 2. disabled(2) -disables the BFD session for PW from monitoring the interface

hwBfdSessEncapsulationType.name: hwBfdSessEncapsulationType
hwBfdSessEncapsulationType.description: The value of this object identifies the VC encapsulation type on an SPE. The values are as follows: fr atm-aal5-sdu atm-trans-cell vlan ethernet hdlc ppp atm-nto1-vcc atm-nto1-vpc ip-layer2 atm-1to1-vcc atm-1to1-vpc atm-aal5-pdu satop-e1 satop-t1 esopsn-basic ip-interworking

hwBfdSessPEVid.name: hwBfdSessPEVid
hwBfdSessPEVid.description: The value of this object identifies the outer tag of a sub-interface for QinQ VLAN tag termination or the VLAN ID of a sub-interface for dot1q VLAN tag termination.

hwBfdSessCEVid.name: hwBfdSessCEVid
hwBfdSessCEVid.description: The value of this object identifies the inner tag in QinQ packets.

hwBfdSessPeerInetAddrType.name: hwBfdSessPeerInetAddrType
hwBfdSessPeerInetAddrType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of the destination address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessPeerInetAddr.name: hwBfdSessPeerInetAddr
hwBfdSessPeerInetAddr.description: The value of this object identifies the destination IP address of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessInetNextHopType.name: hwBfdSessInetNextHopType
hwBfdSessInetNextHopType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of the next hop of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessInetNextHop.name: hwBfdSessInetNextHop
hwBfdSessInetNextHop.description: The value of this object identifies the next hop of the BFD session.

hwBfdSessBindAppTypeMask.name: hwBfdSessBindAppTypeMask
hwBfdSessBindAppTypeMask.description: A value which indicates the set of applications that this BFD session binds. Every bit indicates a application. The corresponding bit and applications are as follows: bit application 0 IFNET 1 Route-Management 2 OSPF 3 ISISL1 4 ISISL2 5 PIM 6 ISISL1L2 7 BGP 8 VRRP 9 LSPM 10 RSVP 11 LDP 12 TE 13 Product Private APP 14 L2VPN 15 OAM_MANAGER 16 VTE 17 VPW 18 MPLSFW 19 VGMP 20 LSPV 21 VSI_PW 22 ETHOAM 23 AUTO 24 E-TRUNK 25 OSPFv3 26 ISISL1_6 27 ISISL2_6 28 PIM6 29 ISISL1L2_6 30 BGP6 31 RM6 32 RBS 33 RIP 34 FRP 35 BGPLSP

hwBfdSessDscp.name: hwBfdSessDscp
hwBfdSessDscp.description: This is the dscp value of bfd packet. 255 is invalid value.

hwBfdSessionPerTable.name: hwBfdSessionPerTable
hwBfdSessionPerTable.description: This table specifies BFD Session performance counters. The index of this table is hwBfdSessPerIndex.

hwBfdSessionPerEntry.name: hwBfdSessionPerEntry
hwBfdSessionPerEntry.description: This table specifies BFD Session performance counters. The index of this entry is hwBfdSessPerIndex.

hwBfdSessPerIndex.name: hwBfdSessPerIndex
hwBfdSessPerIndex.description: The index of BFD session statistics. This index is automatically allocated inside the system and is not user-configurable.

hwBfdSessPerfPktIn.name: hwBfdSessPerfPktIn
hwBfdSessPerfPktIn.description: The statistical information of the received Octets in local system in this session.The total received packet number.

hwBfdSessPerfPktInHC.name: hwBfdSessPerfPktInHC
hwBfdSessPerfPktInHC.description: The statistical information of the received Octets in local system in this session.The high 4 bytes of total received packet number.

hwBfdSessPerfPktOut.name: hwBfdSessPerfPktOut
hwBfdSessPerfPktOut.description: The statistical information of the send Packets in local system in this session.

hwBfdSessPerfPktOutHC.name: hwBfdSessPerfPktOutHC
hwBfdSessPerfPktOutHC.description: The statistical information of the send Packets in local system in this session.The high 4 bytes of total send packet number.

hwBfdSessPerfBadIn.name: hwBfdSessPerfBadIn
hwBfdSessPerfBadIn.description: The statistical information of the received Errors in local system in this session.

hwBfdSessPerfBadInHC.name: hwBfdSessPerfBadInHC
hwBfdSessPerfBadInHC.description: The statistical information of the received Errors in local system in this session.The high 4 bytes of total received wrong packet number.

hwBfdSessPerfBadOut.name: hwBfdSessPerfBadOut
hwBfdSessPerfBadOut.description: The statistical information of the send Errors in local system in this session.

hwBfdSessPerfBadOutHC.name: hwBfdSessPerfBadOutHC
